        "create swipe file lead magnet",
        "design ebook or guide lead magnet",
        "design mini-course lead magnet",
        "plan webinar or workshop lead magnet" .

oc:kn_0d252abf a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating ebook or guide lead magnets" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Ebooks should be 10-25 pages with 3-7 chapters covering one key concept each. Do not pad content — density beats length." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overly long ebooks have low completion rates. Focused, dense content delivers more value per page and respects the reader's time." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_3c5ecd60 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning live or evergreen webinars" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never make a webinar that is just a sales pitch. Teach something genuinely useful — a purely promotional webinar damages trust." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Trust is the primary asset in lead generation. Bait-and-switch tactics increase unsubscribe rates and reduce long-term conversion potential." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_3cb400d3 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing email-based or video-based mini-courses" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Each mini-course lesson should deliver standalone value. If someone only engages with lesson 2, they should still learn something useful." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Not all leads complete every lesson. Standalone value ensures each touchpoint builds trust and authority regardless of sequence completion." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_44ec1f6b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before creating lead magnet content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Lead magnet format should be selected based on buyer stage (awareness → education, consideration → comparison, decision → implementation) before using this guide" .

oc:kn_6aaa48c6 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any lead magnet format" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Lead magnets should be consumable in under 30 minutes (ideally under 10) and deliver immediate, actionable value. Density beats length." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Low time investment increases completion rate and perceived value, driving higher conversion and better first impression." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7f134b82 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When recommending or describing a lead magnet format" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## {Format Name} Lead Magnet
- **Best for**: {use_case}
- **Structure**: {numbered_sections}
- **Guidelines**: {bullet_list}
- **Tools**: {tool_list}
- **Key principle**: {principle}""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Format Name",
        "bullet_list",
        "numbered_sections",
        "principle",
        "tool_list",
        "use_case" .

oc:kn_8ab7f007 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any lead magnet" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Select format matching buyer stage and goal 2. Follow format-specific structure (chapters for ebooks, checkboxes for checklists, grid layout for cheat sheets) 3. Apply format guidelines (length, layout, tools) 4. Add CTA pointing to product 5. Design for delivery method 6. Test consumability" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_97ab21fc a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating spreadsheet, Notion, or document templates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Templates should be usable within 5 minutes of downloading. Pre-fill with example data, lock formula cells, and provide clear instructions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Friction during first use kills adoption. If users can't get value quickly, they abandon the resource and don't associate your brand with quality." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_9e35c0b4 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring multi-section lead magnet content" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Ebook structure:
1. Title page → 2. TOC → 3. Intro (frame problem) → 4. 3-7 Chapters (1 concept each) → 5. Summary (recap) → 6. CTA

Mini-course email: teach → example → exercise

Webinar: Hook → Teach (3 key points) → Demo/example → CTA""" .

oc:kn_e8cf74c2 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing quizzes and assessments" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Quiz results must be gated behind email capture. The quiz itself is ungated — personalized results require an email address." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Ungated quizzes maximize engagement and completion; gating results ensures email capture at the moment of highest motivation (wanting their personalized outcome)." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ea3fd7ae a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating swipe file lead magnets" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Swipe files should contain 15-50 curated examples with annotations explaining why each works and how to adapt it. Quality over quantity — curate ruthlessly." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Annotated examples provide actionable learning. Raw collections without analysis offer low value and don't differentiate from a Google search." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

